OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 1 Jun to Wed 10 JunFA
OL,6,Fchangeable period, as a sequence of
OL,7,FAtlantic weather systems move in from
OL,8,Fthe west to bring a mixture of drier
OL,9,Fspells and some showers or longer
OL,10,Fspells of rain at times. The best of
OL,11,Fthe drier conditions are more likely
OL,12,Ftowards the south and east, with the
OL,13,Frain generally more frequent in parts
OL,14,Fof the west and northwest, although
OL,15,Fthere will be drier interludes here
OL,16,Falso. Temperatures will be near-normal
OL,17,Foverall, with the warmest spots most
OL,18,Flikely across eastern areas. It will
OL,19,Falso be breezy at times, most
OL,20,Fespecially across northwestern areas.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
